How Assistant recognizes your child
You can set up parental controls after you create a Google Account for your child (if they don’t have one yet), which you can do using the Google Family Link app.

Then you can set up Voice Match, and optionally Face Match for certain devices, so Assistant can recognize them. That way you can set different settings for different children, and adults can still get the same experience they’re used to.

What you can control
You can set up media filters to block explicit music or videos for your child. You can choose whether your child has access to certain Assistant features, like making calls.

If you’d like your child to take a break from smart displays & speakers, you can also schedule Downtime.

Works with smart displays & speakers
These parental control settings work with only the smart displays & speakers in your home. You can set up controls for some of the other devices your child uses through the Family Link app.
